# Cursed Japan ARPG — Milestone Task List (MVP → Chapter 1 Playable)

> Assumptions:
> - Solo dev or very small team.
> - 6–8 weeks part-time (or 3–4 weeks full-time) to reach Chapter 1 playable.
> - Tech stack: React + Phaser + TypeScript, using the previously defined architecture.

---

## Milestone 0 — Project Setup (1–2 days)

**Goal:** Have a clean monorepo ready with React + Phaser + TS wired, plus base folder structure.

### Tasks
- [ ] Create repo `cursed-japan-arpg` (or reuse existing monorepo structure).
- [ ] Initialize Vite + React + TypeScript project in `client/`.
- [ ] Install dependencies:
  - [ ] `react`, `react-dom`, `zustand`
  - [ ] `phaser`
  - [ ] `typescript`, `vite`, `vitest` or `jest`
- [ ] Add base folder structure from `data_model_architecture_v1.md` (engine/, phaser/, screens/, store/, types/, constants/, public/data/).
- [ ] Add ESLint + Prettier config.
- [ ] Set up simple `App.tsx` with one placeholder screen.
- [ ] Commit as `milestone-0-setup`.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] `npm run dev` shows a placeholder React page.
- [ ] TypeScript builds without errors.
- [ ] Folder structure matches spec at high level.

---

## Milestone 1 — Core Engine Skeleton (Week 1)

**Goal:** Implement the six-stage combat pipeline and core types with unit tests, no UI.

### Tasks
- [ ] Create `types/` files: `combat.ts`, `item.ts`, `rune.ts`, `character.ts`, `enemy.ts`, `region.ts`, `boss.ts`, `saveState.ts` using the data model spec.
- [ ] Implement `engine/utils/mathHelpers.ts` (clamp, sumOf, productOf).
- [ ] Implement `constants/gameBalance.ts` with caps + TTK target constants.
- [ ] Implement `engine/combat/damageCalc.ts` per pseudocode:
  - [ ] Stage 1: `buildBase()`
  - [ ] Stage 2: `convertDamage()`
  - [ ] Stage 3: `scaleOffensive()`
  - [ ] Stage 4: `resolveCrit()`
  - [ ] Stage 5: `resolveHitOutcome()`
  - [ ] Stage 6: `applyDefenses()` + `applyToResources()`
- [ ] Implement `engine/combat/dotEngine.ts` with DoT stacking rules.
- [ ] Implement `engine/combat/statusEffects.ts` stub (basic types + TODOs).
- [ ] Write unit tests for 5 test vectors from combat spec.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] All combat unit tests pass (Vectors 1–5).
- [ ] No React or Phaser code yet depends on engine functions.
- [ ] Damage pipeline functions are pure (no side effects).

