## Milestone 2 — Data Bootstrapping & Stores (Week 1–2)

**Goal:** Wire static JSON data for one region, one boss, a handful of runes and items; set up Zustand stores.

### Tasks
- [ ] Create `public/data/` JSON files with minimal entries:
  - [ ] `regions.json` → 1 region: `region_edo_streets` with 3–4 nodes (camp, shrine, boss).
  - [ ] `enemies.json` → 2 enemies: `enemy_ronin`, `enemy_city_guard`.
  - [ ] `bosses.json` → 1 boss: `boss_oni_general` with 2 phases and loot table.
  - [ ] `runes.json` → 2 skill runes, 2 link runes.
  - [ ] `weapons.json` → 2 starter katanas.
  - [ ] `armors.json`, `accessories.json` → 2–3 items each.
  - [ ] `passiveNodes.json` → small web of ~10 nodes.
- [ ] Implement `store/usePlayerStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Base character stats, level, EXP, resource, HP.
  - [ ] Starting two skill runes and one katana equipped.
- [ ] Implement `store/useInventoryStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Equipped slots, bag items.
- [ ] Implement `store/useRuneStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Owned runes, 4 skill slots, equip/unequip actions.
- [ ] Implement `store/useMapStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Current region/node, discovered/cleared nodes, idle farming state.
- [ ] Implement `store/useChapterStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Completed chapters, killed bosses, dialogue flags.
- [ ] Implement `store/useOfflineStore.ts`:
  - [ ] Last online timestamp, pending EXP/materials.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] JSON files load successfully at runtime (e.g. via simple debug screen).
- [ ] Stores can be inspected via React DevTools / logs (no UI yet).
- [ ] You can log out: "Current region: Edo Streets, Node: Market Camp, Player Lv.1 with Katana + 2 skill runes."

