## Milestone 4 — First Battle Loop (Normal Camp) (Week 3)

**Goal:** Implement a basic auto-combat loop vs. a small enemy pack, using engine pipeline.

### Tasks
- [ ] Implement `phaser/PhaserGame.tsx` wrapper to mount Phaser inside React.
- [ ] Implement `phaser/scenes/PreloadScene.ts` to load a placeholder tileset + sprites.
- [ ] Implement `phaser/scenes/BattleScene.ts`:
  - [ ] Draw player sprite and 2–3 enemy sprites.
  - [ ] Handle a simple tick loop (e.g. every 500ms) where:
    - [ ] Player auto-attacks nearest enemy using `resolveDamage()`.
    - [ ] Enemies auto-attack player at their own attackSpeed.
  - [ ] On enemy death, emit `ENEMY_DIED` event with drop results from `dropResolver`.
  - [ ] On player death, emit `PLAYER_DIED` event.
- [ ] Implement `phaser/events/PhaserEventBus.ts` (simple EventEmitter bridge).
- [ ] Implement `hooks/useCombatLoop.ts` to:
  - [ ] Listen to Phaser events.
  - [ ] Apply `hpDamage` to `usePlayerStore` and update enemy HP.
  - [ ] Push lines to a local combat log state.
- [ ] Implement `screens/BattleScreen.tsx` using UI spec:
  - [ ] Player HUD (HP, resource, barrier).
  - [ ] Embed `<PhaserGame />` canvas.
  - [ ] Enemy HUD (HP bars for current enemies).
  - [ ] Combat log (last 5 lines).
  - [ ] [Retreat] button → back to `/map`.
- [ ] On [Fight (Auto)] from World Map, navigate to `/battle` with selected node.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] You can click Market Camp → Fight → see player auto-attacking until all enemies die or player dies.
- [ ] Combat log shows damage numbers from the real damage pipeline, not hard-coded.
- [ ] Drops are emitted as plain JS objects (no UI yet).

