## Milestone 5 — Result/Loot & Inventory Wiring (Week 3–4)

**Goal:** Show loot, equip items, and persist gear changes.

### Tasks
- [ ] Implement `engine/items/dropResolver.ts` using `enemies.json` + `bosses.json`.
- [ ] Implement `screens/ResultScreen.tsx` per UI spec:
  - [ ] EXP gained (with bar animation).
  - [ ] Materials list.
  - [ ] Item cards (using `<ItemCard />`).
  - [ ] Buttons: [Fight Again], [Back to Map], [Open Inventory].
- [ ] Implement `<ItemCard />` component:
  - [ ] Shows rarity color, base stats, 3–4 affixes.
  - [ ] [Equip], [Stash], [Sell] buttons.
- [ ] Implement `hooks/useItemEquip.ts`:
  - [ ] Validate slot, level requirement, weapon family.
  - [ ] Update `useInventoryStore` and `usePlayerStore` stats.
- [ ] Implement `screens/InventoryScreen.tsx`:
  - [ ] Equipped gear grid.
  - [ ] Bag grid (6×6).
  - [ ] Detail panel with equip/sell/salvage.
- [ ] Wire: on battle end (all enemies dead) → show ResultScreen modal with loot from dropResolver.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] After winning Market Camp, you see a Result screen with EXP and at least one item.
- [ ] You can equip a new weapon from the Result screen and see stats change in Inventory.
- [ ] Selling an item increases gold.

