## Milestone 7 — Passive Web MVP (Week 5)

**Goal:** Small passive web (~10–15 nodes) with point allocation and stat effects.

### Tasks
- [ ] Implement `engine/runes/passiveWebEngine.ts`:
  - [ ] Validate allocation path (connected to start node).
  - [ ] Sum stats from allocated nodes.
- [ ] Implement `screens/PassiveWebScreen.tsx`:
  - [ ] Render nodes via SVG based on `passiveNodes.json` positions.
  - [ ] Click node → show info → [Allocate] / [Deallocate] buttons.
  - [ ] Point counter at top.
- [ ] Implement `<PassiveNode />` component with visual states (○, ◉, ◆, ◈, ●).
- [ ] On level-up, grant 1 passive point into `usePassiveStore`.
- [ ] When passive state changes, recalculate player stats in `usePlayerStore` using passive web engine.

### Exit criteria
- [ ] Allocating a +Strength node increases player armor/damage as per your stat mapping.
- [ ] Keystone nodes can be unlocked and apply a clearly visible effect (e.g. double-hit with damage penalty).
- [ ] Passive web can be zoomed/panned on desktop; mobile can at least scroll.

